edu.udel.cis.taschd.course

Class Section

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.udel.cis.taschd.course.Section
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Section>

    public class Section
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Section>

    The Section class contains the attributes for each Section. There is a relationship between lab and lecture sections for course instances of a given instructor. If a CourseInstance's CourseInstance.isHasLab() attribute is TRUE, there is a corresponding lecture section for that lab section. For example, Fall 2018 CISC 675 Software Engineer's lecture section is "010" and the CourseInstance.isHasLab() is TRUE, therefore, the lab section for this CourseInstance is "020L". Note that Courses CISC 106 and CISC 108 are the only 2 Courses that require lab assistants, as specified by Dr. Daniel Chester.

    Sections are belong to a Course.

      • Section

        public Section(java.lang.String sectionType,
               java.lang.String sectionNumber,
               java.lang.String instructorName,
               int currentEnrollment,
               int enrollmentCap,
               java.lang.String location,
               WeeklySchedule schedule)
        Constructs a new Section with given CourseInstance for a specified term.
        Parameters:
        sectionType - the type of section which is either lecture (LEC) or lab (LAB), a String.
        sectionNumber - the university 3-digit section identifier, a String consisting of only digits with leading zeros (0).
        instructorName - the instructor's full name who is teaching this Section, a comma-separated proper-case String such as "LastName, FirstName".
        currentEnrollment - the number currently enrolled in this Section, an integer in the range [0,enrollmentCap].
        enrollmentCap - the max number of students that can enroll in this Section, an integer predetermined by the university.
        location - the university 3-character building name and 3-digit room number identifier, a String with a 3-character prefix of only capital letters and a 3-digit post-fix of integers in the range of [000-999].
        schedule - the WeeklySchedule that this Section will meet, an ordered set of TimeIntervals.

      • isMtac

        public boolean isMtac()
        A getter to get the mtac attribute initialized, represented as a boolean value where TRUE indicates that the Section requires mandatory attendance of a teacher's assistant and FALSE indicates that the Section does not require mandatory attendance of a teacher's assistant. Note that if mtac is TRUE, there must be no overlap with the schedule and the CourseAssistant.wtps. On the contrary, if mtac is FALSE, then the schedule can overlap with the CourseAssistant.getWtps().
        Returns:
        mtac True if this Section has a mandatory teacher's assistant requirement.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Section that)

        The order is determined by first comparing prefix. If prefix are equal, courseCode is compared to break the tie. If courseCode is equal, courseName is compared to break the tie. If courseName is equal, both course objects are equal.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Section>
